title: For Sale:  Remington Model 32 Skeet 28" pre Krieghoff Vent Rib like Browning Beretta Perazzi Blaser SKB
postcontent: Up for sale is a Remington model 32 Skeet with 28" barrels. This gun is not mint as it has some carry / use wear on the bluing and a few stock dings. The wear seems correct for a gun of this age that has seen use as a skeet or hunting gun. Although it show some honest signs of use, it has been maintained very well. The bluing is excellent overall with thinning on the bottom of the receiver and trigger guard, where you would expect from a gun this old. The stock has a couple of small dings and light scratches, but no big gouges or cracks. The pictures do not do the stock justice. It is beautiful with amazing grain and color. I'm not sure if the vent rib is factory or if it is a period correct, Simmons or Money Maker. This gun does not appear to have been refinished or modified. It has the factory Remington butt plate. It is tight on face and locking lever is right of center when closed. It also has a few thousands gap on the locking ears when closed, indicating that it has a lot of life left before it would need to be reworked. Barrel selector, and ejectors work perfect. Bores are bright and shiny. Both barrels are marked "SKEET" in the correct factory stamping. One thing that is interestin is that the "skeet" stampings look like they are over "imp" markings which is the way the earliest Skeet barrels were marked. Serial numbers match on the barrels and receiver. Serial number is 4407 indicating manufacture of 1937 according to the BB of Gun Values #22. Length of pull is 14 1/4" to the factory butt plate. I have shot skeet with this gun and it works perfect. Excellent trigger, barrel selector works perfect, and ejection is crisp. I wouldn't hesitate to use this gun as a high volume clays gun. It should be good for 10s of thousands of rounds and any gunsmith who can work on a K32 / Krieghoff 32 should be able to handle any maintenance issues. Make sure your receiving FFL will receive from an individual. If the gun must be shipped from an FFL then add $35 to the total. Please ask any questions
